OL,3,CTata's plans to close blast furnaces
OL,4,Cat Port Talbot 'pretty much' done deal
OL,6,FChief executive TV Narendran told the
OL,7,FWelsh Affairs Committee that Tata had
OL,8,Finvested billions of pounds into Port
OL,9,FTalbot over the past 15 years, but had
OL,10,Freached the stage where decisions
OL,11,Fabout the future had to be made.
OL,13,FCommittee chairman Stephen Crabb
OL,14,F(Conservative, Preseli), asked Mr
OL,15,FNarendran bluntly "At what point does
OL,16,FTata's plan become a "done deal?".
