OL,6,F"The 2,800 job losses proposed are
OL,7,Fjust the tip of the iceberg because of
OL,8,Fthe knock-on effect on people who work
OL,9,Fin the logistic supply chain, nearby
OL,10,Fcafes where workers buy their bacon
OL,11,Fbutties, and even dance schools
OL,12,Fattended by steelworkers' children,"
OL,13,Fshe said.
OL,15,F"We have one member who signed a
OL,16,Fmortgage agreement two weeks before
OL,17,Fthis announcement was made, and a
OL,18,Fsenior union rep in his late 20s who
OL,19,Fwants a job for the next 50 or 60
OL,20,Fyears.
